gmd:title.gco:CharacterString: European air quality data (interpolated data)- Series

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: The data set provides air pollutants concentrations grids combining monitoring air quality data in a ‘regression-interpolation-merging mapping’ methodology and the observational values of the air quality monitoring stations used in the interpolation. It covers Europe on an annual basis. It provides estimates for human health related indicators of pollutants PM10 (annual average, 90.4 percentile of daily means), PM2.5 (annual average), ozone (93.2 percentile of maximum daily 8-hour means, SOMO35, SOMO10) and NO2 (annual average), and vegetation related ozone indicators (AOT40 for vegetation and for forests). The data set contains also Phytotoxic ozone dose (POD) for wheat, tomato and potato and NOx annual average grids.
